models think they will,

00:01:35.150 --> 00:01:38.150 align:middle line:10%
how the National Weather Service
fails forecast after forecast,

00:01:38.150 --> 00:01:43.040 align:middle line:10%
and us as the last front
before-- I should say,

00:01:43.040 --> 00:01:45.520 align:middle line:10%
the interface between the
station and the people.

00:01:45.520 --> 00:01:47.330 align:middle line:90%
We were responsible.

00:01:47.330 --> 00:01:50.320 align:middle line:84%
And it was in the
late '90s to all

00:01:50.320 --> 00:01:52.940 align:middle line:84%
of the first part of the
2000s when I was on the air

00:01:52.940 --> 00:01:56.210 align:middle line:84%
that it was very challenging
to forecast a storm.

00:01:56.210 --> 00:01:59.690 align:middle line:84%
Even here, where we are
in the Mountain West,

00:01:59.690 --> 00:02:01.550 align:middle line:84%
and through the
summer monsoon, there

00:02:01.550 --> 00:02:03.370 align:middle line:84%
were days where it
should have rained.

00:02:03.370 --> 00:02:05.850 align:middle line:84%
I mean, just within the
last two or three weeks.

00:02:05.850 --> 00:02:06.650 align:middle line:90%
And it didn't.

00:02:06.650 --> 00:02:07.880 align:middle line:90%
Time after time after time--

00:02:07.880 --> 00:02:09.679 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And snow
falling in Miami.

00:02:09.679 --> 00:02:10.970 align:middle line:90%
>>STEVENS: What's up with that?

00:02:10.970 --> 00:02:12.219 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: What's up with that?

00:02:12.219 --> 00:02:15.050 align:middle line:84%
>>STEVENS: But it was like
I-- throw your arms up.

00:02:15.050 --> 00:02:16.440 align:middle line:90%
I can't do this anymore.

00:02:16.440 --> 00:02:19.880 align:middle line:84%
And I don't want to
be wrong because I

00:02:19.880 --> 00:02:23.030 align:middle line:90%
can't talk about why I'm wrong.

00:02:23.030 --> 00:02:25.720 align:middle line:84%
If you are forbidden from
talking about geoengineering

00:02:25.720 --> 00:02:28.250 align:middle line:84%
or weather manipulation,
then the responsibility

00:02:28.250 --> 00:02:30.800 align:middle line:84%
for the failed forecasts
rests on the shoulders

00:02:30.800 --> 00:02:32.057 align:middle line:90%
of the meteorologist.

00:02:32.057 --> 00:02:33.890 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And you knew
about geoengineering.

00:02:33.890 --> 00:02:35.120 align:middle line:90%
>>STEVENS: In time I did.

00:02:35.120 --> 00:02:36.530 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, I did.

00:02:36.530 --> 00:02:39.080 align:middle line:84%
By 2004 it became very
apparent that there

00:02:39.080 --> 00:02:41.651 align:middle line:84%
was something terribly
wrong with our weather.

00:02:41.651 --> 00:02:43.400 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Did you ever
talk to management?

00:02:43.400 --> 00:02:44.200 align:middle line:90%
>>STEVENS: Mm-hm.

00:02:44.200 --> 00:02:45.220 align:middle line:90%
Oh, they talked to me.

00:02:45.220 --> 00:02:46.020 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:02:46.020 --> 00:02:48.890 align:middle line:90%
And so, what was that talk like?

00:02:48.890 --> 00:02:52.430 align:middle line:84%
>>STEVENS: Because there was one
day that I kind of went public,

00:02:52.430 --> 00:02:55.560 align:middle line:84%
and, you know, offered
up my credentials saying,

00:02:55.560 --> 00:03:00.350 align:middle line:84%
yeah, what I am saying comes
from a position of knowledge.

00:03:00.350 --> 00:03:04.310 align:middle line:84%
A position of wisdom with
this field of science.

00:03:04.310 --> 00:03:07.160 align:middle line:84%
And it was that next day that
my general manager called me

00:03:07.160 --> 00:03:10.766 align:middle line:84%
up and said, Scott,
what's going on?

00:03:10.766 --> 00:03:11.770 align:middle line:90%
Something's up.

00:03:11.770 --> 00:03:14.240 align:middle line:84%
Well, you're very, very
valuable, but something's up.

00:03:14.240 --> 00:03:15.270 align:middle line:90%
And so I told them.

00:03:15.270 --> 00:03:16.070 align:middle line:90%
I told them.

00:03:16.070 --> 00:03:17.444 align:middle line:84%
I said, this is
what's happening,

00:03:17.444 --> 00:03:21.560 align:middle line:84%
and this is my story, and I
kind of need to be true to this.

00:03:21.560 --> 00:03:23.300 align:middle line:84%
And he kind of
patted me on the back

00:03:23.300 --> 00:03:25.730 align:middle line:90%
and said, OK, I'll honor that.

00:03:25.730 --> 00:03:28.550 align:middle line:90%
And just do it on your own time.

00:03:28.550 --> 00:03:29.732 align:middle line:90%
And I was OK with that.

00:03:29.732 --> 00:03:31.190 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But you
still were giving

00:03:31.190 --> 00:03:34.190 align:middle line:90%
inaccurate forecasts, right?

00:03:34.190 --> 00:03:39.440 align:middle line:84%
Or did you start taking into
account the geoengineering

00:03:39.440 --> 00:03:41.060 align:middle line:84%
and say, OK, I can
make a forecast

00:03:41.060 --> 00:03:42.920 align:middle line:90%
based on what they're spraying.

00:03:42.920 --> 00:03:44.150 align:middle line:90%
>>STEVENS: No, not even that.

00:03:44.150 --> 00:03:45.733 align:middle line:84%
Because I didn't
know where the trails

00:03:45.733 --> 00:03:47.510 align:middle line:90%
fit into the scheme of things.

00:03:47.510 --> 00:03:48.720 align:middle line:90%
I didn't know.

00:03:48.720 --> 00:03:50.240 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, you must
have noticed patterns.

00:03:50.240 --> 00:03:51.364 align:middle line:90%
>>STEVENS: Of course I did.

00:03:51.364 --> 00:03:54.860 align:middle line:84%
But I didn't know how they
interfaced with the failed

00:03:54.860 --> 00:03:56.400 align:middle line:90%
forecasts.

00:03:56.400 --> 00:03:58.910 align:middle line:90%
That aha moment hadn't come yet.

00:03:58.910 --> 00:04:01.640 align:middle line:84%
I knew that there was
residence geometry being

00:04:01.640 --> 00:04:04.430 align:middle line:84%
introduced into the atmosphere
to literally shear storms

00:04:04.430 --> 00:04:05.230 align:middle line:90%
apart.

00:04:05.230 --> 00:04:10.040 align:middle line:84%
That HAARP was available to
re-ionize local areas of storms

00:04:10.040 --> 00:04:13.380 align:middle line:84%
and literally take the
life out of a thunderstorm.

00:04:13.380 --> 00:04:16.300 align:middle line:84%
So instead of being all
bubbly and cauliflower-looking

00:04:16.300 --> 00:04:20.779 align:middle line:84%
and aggressive, it becomes
this wimpy-looking ghost

00:04:20.779 --> 00:04:22.430 align:middle line:90%
of its former self.

00:04:22.430 --> 00:04:27.180 align:middle line:84%
And that's what's happened
in the last two decades?

00:04:27.180 --> 00:04:28.280 align:middle line:90%
Three decades?

00:04:28.280 --> 00:04:30.840 align:middle line:84%
And why the West has
had such a drought.

00:04:30.840 --> 00:04:34.420 align:middle line:84%
Why Australia has
had such a drought.

00:04:34.420 --> 00:04:37.290 align:middle line:84%
So they could use these
antennae, these array,

00:04:37.290 --> 00:04:39.710 align:middle line:84%
these apparatuses that
may be underground,

00:04:39.710 --> 00:04:42.450 align:middle line:84%
circling the Arctic and circling
the Southern Hemisphere,

00:04:42.450 --> 00:04:43.250 align:middle line:90%
as well.

00:04:43.250 --> 00:04:46.260 align:middle line:84%
So they can from a
distance create action.

00:04:46.260 --> 00:04:48.390 align:middle line:84%
And then you dope
up the atmosphere

00:04:48.390 --> 00:04:51.120 align:middle line:84%
with these particles
left over by the planes,

00:04:51.120 --> 00:04:54.540 align:middle line:84%
and then you have grip
on the water molecule.

00:04:54.540 --> 00:04:56.790 align:middle line:84%
And so instead of the
cloud getting, yeah,

00:04:56.790 --> 00:04:59.170 align:middle line:84%
let's all get together,
let's create a raindrop.

00:04:59.170 --> 00:05:01.910 align:middle line:84%
No, there's too much in the
way of condensation nuclei

00:05:01.910 --> 00:05:03.090 align:middle line:90%
in the cloud.

00:05:03.090 --> 00:05:05.160 align:middle line:84%
So we end up with lots
and lots of little drops.

00:05:05.160 --> 00:05:07.920 align:middle line:84%
And then if you could add an
electrical charge delivered

00:05:07.920 --> 00:05:11.280 align:middle line:84%
via an aircraft, or from
a HAARP-like apparatus,

00:05:11.280 --> 00:05:14.460 align:middle line:84%
or from a satellite--
all three are possible.

00:05:14.460 --> 00:05:17.700 align:middle line:84%
Then you've got three modes
of getting at the storm.

00:05:17.700 --> 00:05:20.280 align:middle line:84%
Either enhancing it,
saying, let's get together

00:05:20.280 --> 00:05:22.470 align:middle line:84%
and then it's juiced up
and it becomes a tornado,

00:05:22.470 --> 00:05:25.860 align:middle line:84%
or becomes a flood, or
it becomes a hurricane.

00:05:25.860 --> 00:05:27.410 align:middle line:90%
Or the inverse happens.

00:05:27.410 --> 00:05:28.590 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: In a drought.

00:05:28.590 --> 00:05:29.881 align:middle line:90%
>>STEVENS: And nothing happens.

00:05:29.881 --> 00:05:32.106 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And a lot
of this is detailed,

00:05:32.106 --> 00:05:33.480 align:middle line:84%
and I think it's
done quite well.

00:05:33.480 --> 00:05:35.105 align:middle line:84%
And why in the world
are they spraying?

00:05:35.105 --> 00:05:38.749 align:middle line:84%
In terms of looking at how
the spraying happens, where

00:05:38.749 --> 00:05:40.290 align:middle line:84%
you start off the
coast of California

00:05:40.290 --> 00:05:42.570 align:middle line:84%
to get an effect a few
days later in the Midwest.

00:05:42.570 --> 00:05:43.410 align:middle line:84%
>>STEVENS: Or you
start in Japan.

00:05:43.410 --> 00:05:44.940 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Or you
start in Japan, right.

00:05:44.940 --> 00:05:46.270 align:middle line:84%
>>STEVENS: And engineer
the whole Pacific.

00:05:46.270 --> 00:05:47.070 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Exactly.

00:05:47.070 --> 00:05:51.210 align:middle line:84%
But the point being if they
have the ability-- they do

00:05:51.210 --> 00:05:53.550 align:middle line:84%
have the ability to
simply engineer weather

00:05:53.550 --> 00:05:55.110 align:middle line:90%
wherever they wish now.

00:05:55.110 --> 00:05:57.080 align:middle line:84%
So there are no
excuses for droughts,

00:05:57.080 --> 00:05:59.310 align:middle line:90%
such as what California has had.

00:05:59.310 --> 00:06:02.160 align:middle line:84%
So that starts getting
into some other really

00:06:02.160 --> 00:06:05.100 align:middle line:84%
interesting-- but to me,
some of the most nefarious--

00:06:05.100 --> 00:06:06.090 align:middle line:90%
parts of this agenda.

00:06:06.090 --> 00:06:07.734 align:middle line:84%
And I want to say
right up front,

00:06:07.734 --> 00:06:09.900 align:middle line:84%
we are going to be looking
at the solutions in this.

00:06:09.900 --> 00:06:12.040 align:middle line:84%
This is not just going
to be ranting on.

00:06:12.040 --> 00:06:15.480 align:middle line:84%
But we need to see the
complexity of the issue first.

00:06:15.480 --> 00:06:17.210 align:middle line:90%
So, let's go into it.

00:06:17.210 --> 00:06:19.830 align:middle line:84%
>>STEVENS: That was the whole
reason why I wanted to do this.

00:06:19.830 --> 00:06:21.630 align:middle line:84%
So we could get
public oversight.

00:06:21.630 --> 00:06:22.630 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:06:22.630 --> 00:06:23.430 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:06:23.430 --> 00:06:24.750 align:middle line:84%
>>STEVENS: Because if
there's nobody saying,

00:06:24.750 --> 00:06:25.830 align:middle line:90%
what's going on here?

00:06:25.830 --> 00:06:27.600 align:middle line:90%
Why are you doing this?

00:06:27.600 --> 00:06:29.415 align:middle line:90%
They get a free pass.

00:06:29.415 --> 00:06:31.680 align:middle line:90%
And that's unacceptable.

00:06:31.680 --> 00:06:33.530 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: They do, and they are.

00:06:33.530 --> 00:06:35.470 align:middle line:84%
Because no one even
knows who "they" are.

00:06:35.470 --> 00:06:35.850 align:middle line:90%
>>STEVENS: No.

00:06:35.850 --> 00:06:37.530 align:middle line:84%
But the only thing
I can say to that--

00:06:37.530 --> 00:06:39.279 align:middle line:84%
and we'll get to the
solution at the end--

00:06:39.279 --> 00:06:42.330 align:middle line:90%
is those who can afford it.

00:06:42.330 --> 00:06:45.690 align:middle line:84%
And when you have unlimited
funds at your behest,

00:06:45.690 --> 00:06:48.930 align:middle line:84%
then things-- amazing
things-- can happen.

00:06:48.930 --> 00:06:50.940 align:middle line:90%
It's just without oversight.

00:06:50.940 --> 00:06:53.460 align:middle line:84%
Things can get rather
dark and rather ugly

00:06:53.460 --> 00:06:54.647 align:middle line:90%
and rather nefarious.

00:06:54.647 --> 00:06:56.730 align:middle line:84%
There is another comment,
because you brought up--

00:06:56.730 --> 00:06:59.220 align:middle line:84%
why in the world
are they spraying?

00:06:59.220 --> 00:07:03.210 align:middle line:84%
And thank you, Michael,
for doing that work.

00:07:03.210 --> 00:07:06.040 align:middle line:84%
But the point of the why
was never really addressed.

00:07:06.040 --> 00:07:06.840 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: No.

00:07:06.840 --> 00:07:07.640 align:middle line:90%
It wasn't.

00:07:07.640 --> 00:07:10.830 align:middle line:84%
>>STEVENS: It was largely--
not completely, but largely--

00:07:10.830 --> 00:07:13.110 align:middle line:84%
a rehash of what's
in this stuff.

00:07:13.110 --> 00:07:14.700 align:middle line:90%
And its environmental impacts.

00:07:14.700 --> 00:07:15.630 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: That's true.

00:07:15.630 --> 00:07:16.430 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:07:16.430 --> 00:07:19.440 align:middle line:84%
>>STEVENS: And so this is
where my aha moment came in.

00:07:19.440 --> 00:07:21.840 align:middle line:84%
Because as I was
on the air, seeing

00:07:21.840 --> 00:07:23.747 align:middle line:84%
that we were dealing
with-- literally,

00:07:23.747 --> 00:07:25.830 align:middle line:84%
on the satellite imagery
you can see the patterns.

00:07:25.830 --> 00:07:27.413 align:middle line:84%
You can see the
warming in the clouds.

00:07:27.413 --> 00:07:29.514 align:middle line:84%
You can see the
technology at work.

00:07:29.514 --> 00:07:31.680 align:middle line:84%
And this is something that
on-the-air meteorologists

00:07:31.680 --> 00:07:33.930 align:middle line:84%
either are ignorant
of or are ignoring.

00:07:33.930 --> 00:07:34.960 align:middle line:90%
It's one or the other.

00:07:34.960 --> 00:07:39.150 align:middle line:84%
There is really not
much middle ground.

00:07:39.150 --> 00:07:41.940 align:middle line:84%
But how do you align
this technology?

00:07:41.940 --> 00:07:44.160 align:middle line:90%
How do you target it?

00:07:44.160 --> 00:07:46.320 align:middle line:84%
And that's where
the chemtrails are

00:07:46.320 --> 00:07:51.660 align:middle line:84%
an exquisite, exquisite tool
in delivering these energies

00:07:51.660 --> 00:07:54.790 align:middle line:84%
into the heart of a thunderstorm
or a line of thunderstorms.

00:07:54.790 --> 00:07:57.390 align:middle line:84%
Is that you've got
to mark off and then

00:07:57.390 --> 00:08:01.560 align:middle line:84%
define how much of an impact
this technology has had.

00:08:01.560 --> 00:08:06.060 align:middle line:84%
And so you have a trail
which, despite the blue sky,

00:08:06.060 --> 00:08:08.580 align:middle line:84%
persists from
horizon to horizon.

00:08:08.580 --> 00:08:09.423 align:middle line:90%
Come on now.

00:08:09.423 --> 00:08:10.342 align:middle line:90%
Come on now!

00:08:10.342 --> 00:08:11.550 align:middle line:90%
It shouldn't be there at all.

00:08:11.550 --> 00:08:13.620 align:middle line:84%
These engines are
engineered not to leave

00:08:13.620 --> 00:08:15.540 align:middle line:90%
a trail in the first place.

00:08:15.540 --> 00:08:19.110 align:middle line:84%
And the reason for that is so
condensation trails are not

00:08:19.110 --> 00:08:23.325 align:middle line:84%
mixed up with the fake
trails, which are 99.8% of all

00:08:23.325 --> 00:08:24.410 align:middle line:90%
of the other trails.

00:08:24.410 --> 00:08:25.565 align:middle line:90%
They're all fake.

00:08:25.565 --> 00:08:26.892 align:middle line:90%
Even the short ones.

00:08:26.892 --> 00:08:28.350 align:middle line:84%
Because if you look
at them and you

00:08:28.350 --> 00:08:30.224 align:middle line:84%
happen to have one cross
in front of the sun,

00:08:30.224 --> 00:08:31.792 align:middle line:90%
you'll see a different color.

00:08:31.792 --> 00:08:33.000 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: The rainbow effect.

00:08:33.000 --> 00:08:36.690 align:middle line:84%
>>STEVENS: Some are orange, some
are blue, and a few are white.

00:08:36.690 --> 00:08:39.059 align:middle line:84%
But they all have different
chemical compositions,

00:08:39.059 --> 00:08:42.780 align:middle line:84%
depending on what
they're up there to do.

00:08:42.780 --> 00:08:45.210 align:middle line:84%
The size of the
particle left in.

00:08:45.210 --> 00:08:48.300 align:middle line:84%
If they're meant to
literally smear out

00:08:48.300 --> 00:08:50.700 align:middle line:84%
so you can see the waves that
are happening in the sky.

00:08:50.700 --> 00:08:54.540 align:middle line:84%
Because rarely will a
trail remain straight.

00:08:54.540 --> 00:08:56.010 align:middle line:90%
It'll break.

00:08:56.010 --> 00:08:57.300 align:middle line:90%
It'll twist.

00:08:57.300 --> 00:08:59.912 align:middle line:84%
It'll smear and spread out
while a portion of it remains--

00:08:59.912 --> 00:09:01.620 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Feather out,
zigzag, all of it.

00:09:01.620 --> 00:09:02.190 align:middle line:90%
Zippers.

00:09:02.190 --> 00:09:02.367 align:middle line:90%
>>STEVENS: Yeah.

00:09:02.367 --> 00:09:02.545 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:09:02.545 --> 00:09:03.345 align:middle line:90%
Zip.

00:09:03.345 --> 00:09:04.650 align:middle line:90%
This will happen.

00:09:04.650 --> 00:09:07.860 align:middle line:84%
All of that is simply there
to make these invisible waves,

00:09:07.860 --> 00:09:10.500 align:middle line:84%
these invisible
technologies visible.

00:09:10.500 --> 00:09:12.560 align:middle line:84%
So the yahoos doing
it go, oh, yeah.

00:09:12.560 --> 00:09:13.360 align:middle line:90%
This one's working.

00:09:13.360 --> 00:09:14.700 align:middle line:90%
See, look at this.

00:09:14.700 --> 00:09:19.250 align:middle line:84%
And the most-- the reveal
for me was that once

00:09:19.250 --> 00:09:22.770 align:middle line:84%
you see these anomalies or
perturbations showing up

00:09:22.770 --> 00:09:25.020 align:middle line:84%
in the trails, and
another plane comes along.

00:09:25.020 --> 00:09:27.470 align:middle line:84%
So, say we've had a trail
come along here and it breaks,

00:09:27.470 --> 00:09:28.730 align:middle line:90%
turns off to one side.

00:09:28.730 --> 00:09:32.780 align:middle line:84%
Another plane will come along,
hit that spot precisely,

00:09:32.780 --> 00:09:36.310 align:middle line:84%
also at the angle that the
other trail is breaking off,

00:09:36.310 --> 00:09:37.430 align:middle line:90%
or smearing.

00:09:37.430 --> 00:09:38.960 align:middle line:90%
It's exquisite.

00:09:38.960 --> 00:09:41.510 align:middle line:84%
And you see this if-- you
know, everybody's phone,

00:09:41.510 --> 00:09:43.640 align:middle line:84%
you can download
a time-lapse app.

00:09:43.640 --> 00:09:45.610 align:middle line:90%
Cheap. $2, $3 tops.

00:09:45.610 --> 00:09:49.310 align:middle line:84%
Set it up on a tripod
on a chemtrail day.

00:09:49.310 --> 00:09:51.950 align:middle line:84%
Every five seconds,
take a bloody picture.

00:09:51.950 --> 00:09:55.490 align:middle line:84%
And you'll see this happen,
verifying for yourself

00:09:55.490 --> 00:09:57.590 align:middle line:84%
that these flights
are not willy-nilly.

00:09:57.590 --> 00:09:59.560 align:middle line:84%
They're not random
scratch marks.

00:09:59.560 --> 00:10:00.620 align:middle line:90%
There's a precision.

00:10:00.620 --> 00:10:02.355 align:middle line:84%
It is an exquisite
ballet in the sky.

00:10:02.355 --> 00:10:04.490 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I've even
seen them do U-turns.

00:10:04.490 --> 00:10:05.410 align:middle line:90%
>>STEVENS: Me too.

00:10:05.410 --> 00:10:06.110 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: It's like--

00:10:06.110 --> 00:10:06.990 align:middle line:90%
>>STEVENS: I left my luggage.

00:10:06.990 --> 00:10:07.212 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: --wait a minute.

00:10:07.212 --> 00:10:08.820 align:middle line:90%
That is not commercial flight.

00:10:08.820 --> 00:10:09.890 align:middle line:90%
They don't do U-turns.

00:10:09.890 --> 00:10:10.690 align:middle line:90%
>>STEVENS: No.

00:10:10.690 --> 00:10:13.540 align:middle line:84%
But then you can go to the
apps, like FlightAware.

00:10:13.540 --> 00:10:16.130 align:middle line:90%
Or there are numerous apps.

00:10:16.130 --> 00:10:18.530 align:middle line:84%
You can tap on the flight and
you see it there overhead.

00:10:18.530 --> 00:10:21.050 align:middle line:84%
Then it tells you
Southwest flight number 595

00:10:21.050 --> 00:10:23.180 align:middle line:90%
going from here to here.

00:10:23.180 --> 00:10:25.520 align:middle line:90%
The plane turns around.

00:10:25.520 --> 00:10:28.670 align:middle line:84%
All of a sudden that plane is
not going from here to there--

00:10:28.670 --> 00:10:32.210 align:middle line:84%
it's taken on
another designation.

00:10:32.210 --> 00:10:37.270 align:middle line:84%
And so this illusion
is that intense.

00:10:37.270 --> 00:10:38.487 align:middle line:90%
It's that complete.

00:10:38.487 --> 00:10:40.070 align:middle line:84%
Because we're kind
of smart down here.

00:10:40.070 --> 00:10:40.930 align:middle line:90%
And they're smart too.

00:10:40.930 --> 00:10:42.971 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: OK, so let's go
back to the money part.

00:10:42.971 --> 00:10:45.220 align:middle line:90%
OK, let's go back to California.

00:10:45.220 --> 00:10:46.920 align:middle line:84%
>>STEVENS: Are you
sure you want to?

00:10:46.920 --> 00:10:48.860 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, just
this one aspect of it.

00:10:48.860 --> 00:10:53.570 align:middle line:84%
Why in the world would they
starve-- would an agenda

00:10:53.570 --> 00:10:56.900 align:middle line:84%
starve California, the
breadbasket of this country,

00:10:56.900 --> 00:10:58.510 align:middle line:90%
of water for years on end?

00:10:58.510 --> 00:11:01.940 align:middle line:84%
Why would that happen when
the very reverse can also

00:11:01.940 --> 00:11:03.230 align:middle line:90%
be affected?

00:11:03.230 --> 00:11:08.680 align:middle line:84%
>>STEVENS: What economic
benefit is there to abundance?

00:11:08.680 --> 00:11:11.920 align:middle line:84%
It's only in shortages
is money made.

00:11:11.920 --> 00:11:15.460 align:middle line:84%
It's only in crises
where money is made.

00:11:15.460 --> 00:11:18.790 align:middle line:84%
It's only disasters
where money is made.

00:11:18.790 --> 00:11:22.180 align:middle line:84%
Otherwise you have
this flatlined economy.

00:11:22.180 --> 00:11:24.370 align:middle line:84%
It's only in the wake
of a Sandy-type event--

00:11:24.370 --> 00:11:26.080 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: One of
stability and abundance.

00:11:26.080 --> 00:11:27.470 align:middle line:90%
>>STEVENS: Mm-hm, and peace.

00:11:27.470 --> 00:11:28.580 align:middle line:90%
And productivity.

00:11:28.580 --> 00:11:29.380 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:11:29.380 --> 00:11:31.360 align:middle line:84%
It's when the
biosphere, literally

00:11:31.360 --> 00:11:37.090 align:middle line:84%
a slab between too hot, too
cold, too wet, and too dry.

00:11:37.090 --> 00:11:40.210 align:middle line:84%
And then there's this little
bit of piece in between where

00:11:40.210 --> 00:11:42.550 align:middle line:90%
a true productivity has.

00:11:42.550 --> 00:11:45.280 align:middle line:90%
And so it's all about money.

00:11:45.280 --> 00:11:47.220 align:middle line:84%
And there's a
control thing, too.

00:11:47.220 --> 00:11:49.450 align:middle line:84%
And I'm sure there's some
really, really big egos

00:11:49.450 --> 00:11:50.960 align:middle line:90%
involved, as well.

00:11:50.960 --> 00:11:54.700 align:middle line:84%
Because once they figure out
that they can do it-- why would

00:11:54.700 --> 00:11:55.900 align:middle line:90%
we want to stop?

00:11:55.900 --> 00:11:58.000 align:middle line:84%
Why would we want to
give that back up,

00:11:58.000 --> 00:11:59.470 align:middle line:84%
that process back
to Mother Nature

00:11:59.470 --> 00:12:04.060 align:middle line:84%
when we're doing such a really
good job of owning the weather.

00:12:04.060 --> 00:12:06.800 align:middle line:84%
And in the wake of World
War II, and, you know,

00:12:06.800 --> 00:12:08.200 align:middle line:84%
is it going to be
clear on D-Day?

00:12:08.200 --> 00:12:10.432 align:middle line:84%
Or can we see over
Dresden to bomb, or--

00:12:10.432 --> 00:12:11.890 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And we
can understand why

00:12:11.890 --> 00:12:13.681 align:middle line:84%
they would have
sequestered that technology

00:12:13.681 --> 00:12:14.907 align:middle line:90%
for their military advantage.

00:12:14.907 --> 00:12:16.990 align:middle line:84%
I mean, like it or not,
they would do that, right?

00:12:16.990 --> 00:12:18.407 align:middle line:84%
>>STEVENS: 70 years
down the road?

00:12:18.407 --> 00:12:20.073 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: 70 years
down the road, right.

00:12:20.073 --> 00:12:20.890 align:middle line:90%
>>STEVENS: Really?

00:12:20.890 --> 00:12:21.690 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:12:21.690 --> 00:12:25.890 align:middle line:84%
And in the film, which you
were featured in prominently,

00:12:25.890 --> 00:12:28.480 align:middle line:84%
one of the statements made
was that "weather modification

00:12:28.480 --> 00:12:32.560 align:middle line:84%
is the ultimate weapon
of covert warfare"

00:12:32.560 --> 00:12:36.530 align:middle line:84%
because of its ability to create
food shortages, and so forth.

00:12:36.530 --> 00:12:38.170 align:middle line:84%
And what happens
with food shortages?

00:12:38.170 --> 00:12:39.070 align:middle line:90%
Then you have unrest.

00:12:39.070 --> 00:12:42.730 align:middle line:84%
Then you have people in fear,
and you have people revolting,

00:12:42.730 --> 00:12:43.740 align:middle line:90%
and so on and so forth.

00:12:43.740 --> 00:12:44.540 align:middle line:90%
Right?

00:12:44.540 --> 00:12:46.005 align:middle line:90%
>>STEVENS: Mm-hm, all of that.

00:12:46.005 --> 00:12:46.921 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: All of that.

00:12:46.921 --> 00:12:48.634 align:middle line:84%
So that's just one
picture politically,

00:12:48.634 --> 00:12:50.800 align:middle line:84%
if you were going to use
it against another country,

00:12:50.800 --> 00:12:54.200 align:middle line:84%
an enemy country, that you
can create that kind of unrest

00:12:54.200 --> 00:12:56.657 align:middle line:90%
within their population.

00:12:56.657 --> 00:12:58.240 align:middle line:84%
But at the same time,
let's look at it

00:12:58.240 --> 00:13:00.760 align:middle line:84%
from the point of the
disaster capitalist.

00:13:00.760 --> 00:13:01.905 align:middle line:90%
Even in our own country--

00:13:01.905 --> 00:13:02.863 align:middle line:90%
>>STEVENS: Naomi Klein.

00:13:02.863 --> 00:13:05.030 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: --what people
will do to our own people.

00:13:05.030 --> 00:13:06.700 align:middle line:84%
So let's talk about
that at some length,

00:13:06.700 --> 00:13:09.400 align:middle line:84%
because now we're getting into
the connection between this

00:13:09.400 --> 00:13:11.144 align:middle line:84%
and follow the money,
and where we're

00:13:11.144 --> 00:13:12.310 align:middle line:90%
going to go with this story.

00:13:12.310 --> 00:13:16.570 align:middle line:84%
>>STEVENS: And ultimately, if
you hand that technology off

00:13:16.570 --> 00:13:21.012 align:middle line:84%
to corporations, then you
could have a government saying,

00:13:21.012 --> 00:13:23.740 align:middle line:90%
it's not us.

00:13:23.740 --> 00:13:26.670 align:middle line:90%
And then there's deniability.

00:13:26.670 --> 00:13:29.770 align:middle line:84%
Then, we're there
to rally the troops.

00:13:29.770 --> 00:13:31.180 align:middle line:84%
I mean, the whole
purpose of 9/11

00:13:31.180 --> 00:13:33.560 align:middle line:84%
was to get Bush's
approval ratings up

00:13:33.560 --> 00:13:36.010 align:middle line:84%
to into the 90%
range-- and it worked--

00:13:36.010 --> 00:13:39.040 align:middle line:84%
so we could go off adventuring
into the Middle East.

00:13:39.040 --> 00:13:44.980 align:middle line:84%
And so weather can be used as
an emotional turning point.

00:13:44.980 --> 00:13:49.120 align:middle line:84%
If we have so many
disasters, then there's

00:13:49.120 --> 00:13:50.470 align:middle line:90%
got to be a reason for them.

00:13:50.470 --> 00:13:53.140 align:middle line:84%
And Lord knows it's
not geoengineering.

00:13:53.140 --> 00:13:54.490 align:middle line:90%
No, we can't do that yet.

00:13:54.490 --> 00:13:56.410 align:middle line:84%
You know, it's just
it's a pipe dream.

00:13:56.410 --> 00:13:59.035 align:middle line:84%
Maybe something we'll invest in
in the future, but no, no, no,

00:13:59.035 --> 00:13:59.910 align:middle line:90%
we can't do that yet.

00:13:59.910 --> 00:14:01.930 align:middle line:84%
So we all have to
quit driving our cars.

00:14:01.930 --> 00:14:03.180 align:middle line:90%
We all have to drive Priuses.

00:14:03.180 --> 00:14:06.310 align:middle line:84%
We have to, we have to,
and we have to, with CO2.

00:14:06.310 --> 00:14:08.840 align:middle line:84%
No, no, and then we're all
going after wear masks,

00:14:08.840 --> 00:14:11.710 align:middle line:84%
so we sequester our
CO2 because, you know,

00:14:11.710 --> 00:14:13.060 align:middle line:90%
it's all about the CO2.

00:14:13.060 --> 00:14:15.820 align:middle line:84%
You know, plants,
they're a problem too.

00:14:15.820 --> 00:14:18.790 align:middle line:84%
So they've spun this
whole series of lies.

00:14:18.790 --> 00:14:22.690 align:middle line:84%
The ultimate agenda
is a global tax.

00:14:22.690 --> 00:14:24.610 align:middle line:84%
And if they can get
all of these countries

00:14:24.610 --> 00:14:28.930 align:middle line:84%
to sign onto an accord,
a climate-change accord,

00:14:28.930 --> 00:14:31.990 align:middle line:84%
then that gives them
access to water rights,

00:14:31.990 --> 00:14:35.810 align:middle line:84%
atmospheric rights, pollution
rights, energy usage rights,

00:14:35.810 --> 00:14:37.090 align:middle line:90%
health rights.

00:14:37.090 --> 00:14:38.410 align:middle line:90%
All of these things.

00:14:38.410 --> 00:14:42.160 align:middle line:84%
This is the one thing that
all of humanity has in common,

00:14:42.160 --> 00:14:43.790 align:middle line:90%
is the planet.

00:14:43.790 --> 00:14:46.180 align:middle line:84%
And if we turn the
planet against us,

00:14:46.180 --> 00:14:50.160 align:middle line:84%
then we will use that as
the tool to tax everyone

00:14:50.160 --> 00:14:51.989 align:middle line:90%
and to control all aspects of--

00:14:51.989 --> 00:14:53.405 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Carbon
credits and such.

00:14:53.405 --> 00:14:54.550 align:middle line:90%
>>STEVENS: Thank you.

00:14:54.550 --> 00:14:58.570 align:middle line:84%
And then it becomes a whole
other medium for money

00:14:58.570 --> 00:15:00.490 align:middle line:90%
back into the machine.

00:15:00.490 --> 00:15:04.180 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So, fair to say that
your take on global climate

00:15:04.180 --> 00:15:07.360 align:middle line:84%
change is that they can tell
whatever story they want,

00:15:07.360 --> 00:15:09.860 align:middle line:84%
depending on what they choose
to manipulate at a given time.

00:15:09.860 --> 00:15:11.190 align:middle line:84%
That's why it's,
oh, it's cooling.

00:15:11.190 --> 00:15:12.520 align:middle line:90%
Oops, no, it seems to be warm.

00:15:12.520 --> 00:15:14.860 align:middle line:84%
Well, over here it's warming,
over here it's cooling.

00:15:14.860 --> 00:15:15.160 align:middle line:90%
>>STEVENS: Exactly.

00:15:15.160 --> 00:15:16.970 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: That it's all
a matter of manipulation.

00:15:16.970 --> 00:15:17.830 align:middle line:90%
It's not organic.

00:15:17.830 --> 00:15:20.260 align:middle line:84%
>>STEVENS: And it all-- the
people will believe what

00:15:20.260 --> 00:15:22.880 align:middle line:90%
the mouthpiece of the machine--

00:15:22.880 --> 00:15:24.500 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: The media.

00:15:24.500 --> 00:15:25.720 align:middle line:90%
>>STEVENS: --tells them.

00:15:25.720 --> 00:15:27.370 align:middle line:84%
If we have a problem
with climate.

00:15:27.370 --> 00:15:30.820 align:middle line:84%
And in this regard I have
to applaud the Republicans

00:15:30.820 --> 00:15:34.630 align:middle line:84%
in Congress for standing
up to the Democratic side

00:15:34.630 --> 00:15:38.920 align:middle line:90%
of this illusion.

00:15:38.920 --> 00:15:40.930 align:middle line:90%
Because climate always changes.

00:15:40.930 --> 00:15:43.390 align:middle line:90%
It has never not changed.

00:15:43.390 --> 00:15:44.350 align:middle line:90%
Just like the weather.

00:15:44.350 --> 00:15:46.300 align:middle line:90%
It changes.

00:15:46.300 --> 00:15:47.859 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: It
happens organically.

00:15:47.859 --> 00:15:49.400 align:middle line:84%
I mean, it goes
through these cycles,

00:15:49.400 --> 00:15:52.112 align:middle line:84%
which has to do with solar
input and everything else.

00:15:52.112 --> 00:15:53.570 align:middle line:84%
>>STEVENS: And
orbital precession--

00:15:53.570 --> 00:15:54.040 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Exactly.

00:15:54.040 --> 00:15:54.380 align:middle line:90%
All of it.

00:15:54.380 --> 00:15:54.990 align:middle line:90%
>>STEVENS: All of it.

00:15:54.990 --> 00:15:55.120 align:middle line:90%
Sunspots--

00:15:55.120 --> 00:15:56.620 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And yet
at the same time,

00:15:56.620 --> 00:15:59.620 align:middle line:84%
we now have chemtrails
added to the mix, which is

00:15:59.620 --> 00:16:01.330 align:middle line:90%
to change the climate at will.

00:16:01.330 --> 00:16:05.410 align:middle line:84%
>>STEVENS: So the question
is, what's really happening?

00:16:05.410 --> 00:16:07.030 align:middle line:84%
If we're playing
with the weather,

00:16:07.030 --> 00:16:10.540 align:middle line:84%
is the planet really
warming or is it cooling?

00:16:10.540 --> 00:16:13.300 align:middle line:84%
And if the National Climatic
Data Center in Asheville, North

00:16:13.300 --> 00:16:16.420 align:middle line:84%
Carolina has to truly
come in and seasonally

00:16:16.420 --> 00:16:20.530 align:middle line:84%
adjust the data
aggressively to maintain

00:16:20.530 --> 00:16:24.610 align:middle line:84%
the illusion of warming,
then what's really happening?

00:16:24.610 --> 00:16:25.985 align:middle line:84%
Are we warming or
are we cooling?

00:16:25.985 --> 00:16:26.785 align:middle line:90%
And then you have--

00:16:26.785 --> 00:16:28.119 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: It's really happening.

00:16:28.119 --> 00:16:29.618 align:middle line:84%
>>STEVENS: For me
it's apparent-- we

00:16:29.618 --> 00:16:30.710 align:middle line:90%
ought to go to the sun.

00:16:30.710 --> 00:16:32.980 align:middle line:84%
All of the heat,
all of the energy,

00:16:32.980 --> 00:16:35.800 align:middle line:84%
and essentially the
surface life of this planet

00:16:35.800 --> 00:16:37.280 align:middle line:90%
is dependent on the sun.

00:16:37.280 --> 00:16:38.080 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Totally.

00:16:38.080 --> 00:16:41.020 align:middle line:84%
So what happens when you cut
off huge percentages of that

00:16:41.020 --> 00:16:43.030 align:middle line:84%
on a day-to-day
basis from the sun

00:16:43.030 --> 00:16:46.010 align:middle line:84%
by blocking it with these
chemtrails and reflective

00:16:46.010 --> 00:16:46.810 align:middle line:90%
metals?

00:16:46.810 --> 00:16:47.726 align:middle line:90%
>>STEVENS: Two things.

00:16:47.726 --> 00:16:48.940 align:middle line:90%
Two things can happen.

00:16:48.940 --> 00:16:51.130 align:middle line:84%
Either you're reflecting
enough during the day

00:16:51.130 --> 00:16:54.790 align:middle line:84%
to inhibit
photosynthesis, to inhibit

00:16:54.790 --> 00:16:59.160 align:middle line:84%
the deployment of
solar photovoltaics,

00:16:59.160 --> 00:17:01.090 align:middle line:84%
that you end up with
fallout that impacts

00:17:01.090 --> 00:17:05.619 align:middle line:90%
the pH of soils and oceans.

00:17:05.619 --> 00:17:06.760 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: And people.

00:17:06.760 --> 00:17:09.069 align:middle line:84%
>>STEVENS: And we're just
dealing with the conductivity

00:17:09.069 --> 00:17:10.277 align:middle line:90%
in the atmosphere in general.

00:17:10.277 --> 00:17:12.660 align:middle line:90%
And this is still a side point.

00:17:12.660 --> 00:17:14.890 align:middle line:84%
Because the main
issue is the sun.

00:17:14.890 --> 00:17:18.155 align:middle line:84%
Right The main issue
always has been the sun.

00:17:18.155 --> 00:17:19.030 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I get that.

00:17:19.030 --> 00:17:22.630 align:middle line:84%
>>STEVENS: And so it's
like there's this cliff.

00:17:22.630 --> 00:17:24.855 align:middle line:84%
