let's look at it from
the other point of view.

00:17:58.225 --> 00:17:59.100 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: In reverse.

00:17:59.100 --> 00:17:59.920 align:middle line:90%
Exactly.

00:17:59.920 --> 00:18:01.212 align:middle line:90%
So if they say global warming--

00:18:01.212 --> 00:18:02.420 align:middle line:90%
>>STEVENS: That's an ice age.

00:18:02.420 --> 00:18:03.570 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: --global cooling.

00:18:03.570 --> 00:18:04.200 align:middle line:90%
It's an ice age.

00:18:04.200 --> 00:18:05.325 align:middle line:90%
>>STEVENS: It's an ice age.

00:18:05.325 --> 00:18:07.840 align:middle line:84%
And I think that became
apparent in the '60s and '70s

00:18:07.840 --> 00:18:09.666 align:middle line:84%
because that was
all the discussion.

00:18:09.666 --> 00:18:10.790 align:middle line:90%
There is an ice age coming.

00:18:10.790 --> 00:18:11.770 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, there's an ice age coming.

00:18:11.770 --> 00:18:13.978 align:middle line:84%
And all of a sudden in the
'80s-- no, no, no, no, no,

00:18:13.978 --> 00:18:14.920 align:middle line:90%
it's global warming.

00:18:14.920 --> 00:18:19.600 align:middle line:84%
They had this technology to
delay the arrival of the cold.

00:18:19.600 --> 00:18:22.600 align:middle line:84%
But now the sun is,
each solar cycle,

00:18:22.600 --> 00:18:25.900 align:middle line:84%
the higher the peak, the
more energy, the more warmth

00:18:25.900 --> 00:18:27.250 align:middle line:90%
coming from the sun.

00:18:27.250 --> 00:18:32.020 align:middle line:84%
Each succeeding 22-year cycle
is increasingly shallow.

00:18:32.020 --> 00:18:35.816 align:middle line:84%
And there is a beautiful,
beautiful solar physicist--

00:18:35.816 --> 00:18:37.690 align:middle line:84%
well, beautiful, you
know, it's all relative,

00:18:37.690 --> 00:18:39.940 align:middle line:90%
beauty-- in England.

00:18:39.940 --> 00:18:45.100 align:middle line:84%
And her model of
the magnetics that

00:18:45.100 --> 00:18:48.150 align:middle line:84%
are happening sub-surface of the
sun, and also on the surface,

00:18:48.150 --> 00:18:50.440 align:middle line:90%
are 99.x.

00:18:50.440 --> 00:18:53.370 align:middle line:84%
They are very, very accurate
when you reverse engineer

00:18:53.370 --> 00:18:54.620 align:middle line:90%
what's happening with the sun.

00:18:54.620 --> 00:18:57.280 align:middle line:84%
And she's like, by 2030
we're in an ice age.

00:18:57.280 --> 00:18:59.590 align:middle line:84%
The question is, how
long does it last?

00:18:59.590 --> 00:19:01.630 align:middle line:84%
Is it like the previous
cool spells that we've

00:19:01.630 --> 00:19:02.890 align:middle line:90%
had in previous centuries?

00:19:02.890 --> 00:19:05.200 align:middle line:84%
Or is it truly the
arrival of something

00:19:05.200 --> 00:19:07.600 align:middle line:90%
that lasts 90,000 years?

00:19:07.600 --> 00:19:09.610 align:middle line:90%
I don't have that answer.

00:19:09.610 --> 00:19:12.610 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Do they feel--
so are you saying, then,

00:19:12.610 --> 00:19:17.290 align:middle line:84%
that on one level, while various
interests behind chemtrails

00:19:17.290 --> 00:19:22.550 align:middle line:84%
are profiting hugely from it,
at the same time that there

00:19:22.550 --> 00:19:26.890 align:middle line:84%
is an attempt to modulate
the climate on the Earth

00:19:26.890 --> 00:19:29.019 align:middle line:90%
so the species can continue on?

00:19:29.019 --> 00:19:31.060 align:middle line:84%
I mean, then you look at
someone like Bill Gates.

00:19:31.060 --> 00:19:34.780 align:middle line:84%
Why is he gathering all
of these heirloom seeds

00:19:34.780 --> 00:19:36.020 align:middle line:90%
in a vault in the Arctic?

00:19:36.020 --> 00:19:37.300 align:middle line:90%
I mean, why is that going on?

00:19:37.300 --> 00:19:39.350 align:middle line:90%
Against what kind of disaster?

00:19:39.350 --> 00:19:41.170 align:middle line:84%
>>STEVENS: I think
that we're going

00:19:41.170 --> 00:19:43.610 align:middle line:84%
to go through a pole shift--
a magnetic field pole shift.

00:19:43.610 --> 00:19:46.030 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, and that was
the discussion 20 years ago.

00:19:46.030 --> 00:19:48.155 align:middle line:84%
Gregg Braden really was
central to that discussion,

00:19:48.155 --> 00:19:50.450 align:middle line:84%
and he stopped talking
about it over 15 years ago.

00:19:50.450 --> 00:19:51.250 align:middle line:90%
>>STEVENS: No.

00:19:51.250 --> 00:19:53.920 align:middle line:84%
But if you look at
the mathematics,

00:19:53.920 --> 00:19:57.530 align:middle line:84%
the pace of the pole
change across the north,

00:19:57.530 --> 00:19:58.907 align:middle line:90%
it seems inevitable.

00:19:58.907 --> 00:20:00.490 align:middle line:84%
And all of these
changes are geometric

00:20:00.490 --> 00:20:03.930 align:middle line:90%
in pattern and play-out.

00:20:03.930 --> 00:20:07.130 align:middle line:84%
When it happens, it will happen
very, very, very, very fast.

00:20:07.130 --> 00:20:07.930 align:middle line:90%
Very fast.

00:20:07.930 --> 00:20:09.310 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I wonder-- OK.

