So I'm just going to bring
a little esoterica up

00:20:10.655 --> 00:20:11.170 align:middle line:90%
in the middle of this.

00:20:11.170 --> 00:20:11.620 align:middle line:90%
>>STEVENS: Please.

00:20:11.620 --> 00:20:12.420 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:20:12.420 --> 00:20:14.620 align:middle line:84%
So I was meditating on
that a few years ago.

00:20:14.620 --> 00:20:16.540 align:middle line:90%
I don't remember why, even.

00:20:16.540 --> 00:20:19.300 align:middle line:84%
But I was meditating and just
looking at what was happening.

00:20:19.300 --> 00:20:21.070 align:middle line:84%
And what came up was
kind of surprising.

00:20:21.070 --> 00:20:24.220 align:middle line:84%
And it had to do with odd
storm patterns in the Midwest,

00:20:24.220 --> 00:20:25.420 align:middle line:90%
apparently.

00:20:25.420 --> 00:20:27.859 align:middle line:84%
And what I was seeing--
and you tell me

00:20:27.859 --> 00:20:28.900 align:middle line:90%
whether this is possible.

00:20:28.900 --> 00:20:31.960 align:middle line:84%
I know others have apparently
seen similar things-- is

00:20:31.960 --> 00:20:37.360 align:middle line:84%
that there are these areas
and pockets where the pole,

00:20:37.360 --> 00:20:39.130 align:middle line:84%
essentially the magnetic
field has already

00:20:39.130 --> 00:20:42.730 align:middle line:84%
reversed, in little isolated
pockets around the world.

00:20:42.730 --> 00:20:44.690 align:middle line:90%
That it's already begun.

00:20:44.690 --> 00:20:45.490 align:middle line:90%
Right?

00:20:45.490 --> 00:20:46.015 align:middle line:90%
Is that true?

00:20:46.015 --> 00:20:46.270 align:middle line:90%
>>STEVENS: Mm-hm.

00:20:46.270 --> 00:20:47.811 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: OK, well
that's what I saw.

00:20:47.811 --> 00:20:51.130 align:middle line:84%
Which led me to
think, is it possible

00:20:51.130 --> 00:20:53.380 align:middle line:84%
that this will
continue happening?

00:20:53.380 --> 00:20:56.680 align:middle line:84%
And be more of a gradual
kind of pole shift,

00:20:56.680 --> 00:20:58.930 align:middle line:84%
as more of these places
establish themselves?

00:20:58.930 --> 00:21:03.059 align:middle line:84%
Rather than boom-- from positive
to negative, north to south.

00:21:03.059 --> 00:21:05.350 align:middle line:84%
>>STEVENS: And I don't know
if it's going to be a this.

00:21:05.350 --> 00:21:06.430 align:middle line:90%
It might just be a this.

00:21:06.430 --> 00:21:07.930 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: That's
what I'm wondering,

00:21:07.930 --> 00:21:10.250 align:middle line:84%
because I was seeing that
this is happening all over.

00:21:10.250 --> 00:21:11.050 align:middle line:90%
>>STEVENS: Yeah.

00:21:11.050 --> 00:21:13.420 align:middle line:84%
That we don't have a
complete reversal that way,

00:21:13.420 --> 00:21:15.570 align:middle line:90%
but just simply a readjustment.

00:21:15.570 --> 00:21:16.470 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:21:16.470 --> 00:21:16.720 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:21:16.720 --> 00:21:17.530 align:middle line:90%
And that's--

00:21:17.530 --> 00:21:18.310 align:middle line:90%
>>STEVENS: And I could see--

