I've got two Macs.

00:41:29.800 --> 00:41:31.850 align:middle line:84%
I'm not sitting
there using them.

00:41:31.850 --> 00:41:33.550 align:middle line:90%
So what are they doing?

00:41:33.550 --> 00:41:35.300 align:middle line:90%
Nothing.

00:41:35.300 --> 00:41:36.310 align:middle line:90%
Nothing.

00:41:36.310 --> 00:41:38.200 align:middle line:84%
It's like having two
employees that I'm

00:41:38.200 --> 00:41:42.280 align:middle line:84%
paying, because they're
turned on, doing nothing.

00:41:42.280 --> 00:41:45.160 align:middle line:84%
I've got a phone sitting there,
waiting for me to use it.

00:41:45.160 --> 00:41:46.880 align:middle line:90%
It's doing nothing.

00:41:46.880 --> 00:41:49.270 align:middle line:84%
So there's all of
this processing power.

00:41:49.270 --> 00:41:53.500 align:middle line:84%
Literally millions of
petahashes, all this CPU power,

00:41:53.500 --> 00:41:55.150 align:middle line:90%
doing nothing.

00:41:55.150 --> 00:41:57.850 align:middle line:84%
When this Bitcoin
becomes common knowledge,

00:41:57.850 --> 00:41:59.560 align:middle line:84%
people will put their
computers to work.

00:41:59.560 --> 00:42:00.770 align:middle line:90%
They'll download a program.

00:42:00.770 --> 00:42:02.020 align:middle line:90%
It doesn't have to be Bitcoin.

00:42:02.020 --> 00:42:04.270 align:middle line:84%
There are literally
hundreds of other currencies

00:42:04.270 --> 00:42:07.480 align:middle line:84%
that they can mine, depending on
the capability or the strength

00:42:07.480 --> 00:42:08.980 align:middle line:90%
of their computers.

00:42:08.980 --> 00:42:11.320 align:middle line:84%
So then their computers
are securing the networks,

00:42:11.320 --> 00:42:12.970 align:middle line:84%
processing transactions,
essentially

00:42:12.970 --> 00:42:16.420 align:middle line:84%
doing what a bank does--
and getting rewarded

00:42:16.420 --> 00:42:18.700 align:middle line:90%
in fractions of a coin.

00:42:18.700 --> 00:42:22.810 align:middle line:84%
So my computers are mining
two particular coin.

00:42:22.810 --> 00:42:24.970 align:middle line:84%
I'm not at home, but
yet they're working

00:42:24.970 --> 00:42:28.067 align:middle line:84%
and they're earning me
coins, which are then

00:42:28.067 --> 00:42:29.650 align:middle line:84%
convertible to
Bitcoin, which are then

00:42:29.650 --> 00:42:31.900 align:middle line:90%
convertible to fiat money.

00:42:31.900 --> 00:42:33.340 align:middle line:90%
Spendable money.

00:42:33.340 --> 00:42:36.550 align:middle line:84%
So what will happen when
the next system goes down?

00:42:36.550 --> 00:42:39.700 align:middle line:84%
Either they open the
fire hose and print

00:42:39.700 --> 00:42:41.800 align:middle line:84%
and print and print and
print and print money

00:42:41.800 --> 00:42:44.170 align:middle line:90%
to try to get inflation to go.

00:42:44.170 --> 00:42:47.680 align:middle line:84%
So that our money, our
debts, the government's debts

00:42:47.680 --> 00:42:49.870 align:middle line:90%
are more easily paid off.

00:42:49.870 --> 00:42:53.620 align:middle line:84%
So if you took out of
house loan in 1978--

00:42:53.620 --> 00:42:57.400 align:middle line:84%
let's say it was a $50,000
house-- your house payment is

00:42:57.400 --> 00:42:59.170 align:middle line:90%
under $400.

00:42:59.170 --> 00:43:02.740 align:middle line:84%
Which is very easy to
pay in today's dollars.

00:43:02.740 --> 00:43:05.730 align:middle line:90%
Not so much 30 years ago.

00:43:05.730 --> 00:43:09.410 align:middle line:84%
And this is the beauty
of inflation for them.

00:43:09.410 --> 00:43:11.740 align:middle line:84%
So these currencies,
these cryptocurrencies

00:43:11.740 --> 00:43:12.880 align:middle line:90%
can be deflationary.

00:43:12.880 --> 00:43:14.710 align:middle line:90%
Bitcoin is deflationary.

00:43:14.710 --> 00:43:18.340 align:middle line:84%
Meaning that the value
of the coin goes up.

00:43:18.340 --> 00:43:20.180 align:middle line:90%
So six years ago--

00:43:20.180 --> 00:43:22.660 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Rather than with
currencies where it goes down.

00:43:22.660 --> 00:43:25.090 align:middle line:84%
>>STEVENS: Six years ago
it was worth less than $1.

00:43:25.090 --> 00:43:30.355 align:middle line:84%
Now it's worth, in mid-August of
2016, worth in the $560, $570,

00:43:30.355 --> 00:43:31.940 align:middle line:90%
$580 range.

00:43:31.940 --> 00:43:34.570 align:middle line:84%
Meaning that that
house payment requires

00:43:34.570 --> 00:43:36.815 align:middle line:90%
maybe 6/10, 7/10 of a Bitcoin.

00:43:36.815 --> 00:43:39.460 align:middle line:84%
That $400 house
payment-- or now it's

00:43:39.460 --> 00:43:42.350 align:middle line:84%
a car payment-- at
that price point.

00:43:42.350 --> 00:43:45.970 align:middle line:84%
So as the value of this
coin goes up-- and it will,

00:43:45.970 --> 00:43:48.890 align:middle line:84%
because people, do I
buy government bonds?

00:43:48.890 --> 00:43:49.690 align:middle line:90%
Sure.

00:43:49.690 --> 00:43:51.720 align:middle line:84%
Am I going to give
the government--

00:43:51.720 --> 00:43:53.740 align:middle line:84%
and in the case with
Switzerland, their debt

00:43:53.740 --> 00:43:56.080 align:middle line:84%
after 30 years, the
Swiss or whoever's

00:43:56.080 --> 00:43:58.090 align:middle line:84%
investing in Swiss
government bonds,

00:43:58.090 --> 00:44:01.504 align:middle line:84%
paying them money for that
government to say, hm,

00:44:01.504 --> 00:44:02.920 align:middle line:84%
what are we going
to do with this?

00:44:02.920 --> 00:44:04.210 align:middle line:90%
How do we service our debt?

00:44:04.210 --> 00:44:06.190 align:middle line:84%
And when you get
your bond back, it's

00:44:06.190 --> 00:44:09.100 align:middle line:84%
going to be worth less
than what you paid.

00:44:09.100 --> 00:44:11.350 align:middle line:84%
And this is happening
in Japan and China.

00:44:11.350 --> 00:44:13.774 align:middle line:84%
Not in China yet, but
it's all over the world.

00:44:13.774 --> 00:44:15.940 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So where are
governments in their position

00:44:15.940 --> 00:44:17.800 align:middle line:90%
