And yet, if the Pentagon wanted
to go misspend $2.4 trillion

00:44:50.950 --> 00:44:53.650 align:middle line:84%
with Bitcoin, they would
have to go out and purchase

00:44:53.650 --> 00:44:55.150 align:middle line:90%
that Bitcoin.

00:44:55.150 --> 00:44:57.180 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Didn't they
do that at one point?

00:44:57.180 --> 00:44:57.390 align:middle line:90%
>>STEVENS: No.

00:44:57.390 --> 00:44:57.760 align:middle line:90%
No, no, no, no.

00:44:57.760 --> 00:44:58.810 align:middle line:90%
They're nowhere near it.

00:44:58.810 --> 00:44:59.290 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: No?

00:44:59.290 --> 00:45:00.090 align:middle line:90%
>>STEVENS: No.

00:45:00.090 --> 00:45:02.440 align:middle line:84%
But if they were to
go buy that Bitcoin,

00:45:02.440 --> 00:45:04.450 align:middle line:84%
the value of the Bitcoins
in existence today

00:45:04.450 --> 00:45:07.810 align:middle line:84%
