00:49:48.340 --> 00:49:50.110 align:middle line:90%
the question is, what is it?

00:49:50.110 --> 00:49:54.434 align:middle line:84%
I mean, truly that
is the "what is it?"

00:49:54.434 --> 00:49:55.312 align:middle line:90%
What is money?

00:49:55.312 --> 00:49:57.770 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: It's like a product
of an algorithm of some kind.

00:49:57.770 --> 00:49:57.960 align:middle line:90%
>>STEVENS: Thank you.

00:49:57.960 --> 00:49:59.500 align:middle line:90%
At its most general scale.

00:49:59.500 --> 00:50:00.770 align:middle line:90%
But what is money?

00:50:00.770 --> 00:50:04.420 align:middle line:84%
A unit of accounting, a
store of value, and a medium

00:50:04.420 --> 00:50:05.590 align:middle line:90%
of exchange.

00:50:05.590 --> 00:50:08.050 align:middle line:90%
Those three things define money.

00:50:08.050 --> 00:50:11.410 align:middle line:84%
And yet Bitcoin, because
you determine it has value,

00:50:11.410 --> 00:50:16.402 align:middle line:84%
and there is an open 24/7/365
market for it-- they're

00:50:16.402 --> 00:50:18.610 align:middle line:84%
in China, they're in the
states, they're in-- I mean,

00:50:18.610 --> 00:50:20.740 align:middle line:84%
there are global markets
for this currency.

00:50:20.740 --> 00:50:22.760 align:middle line:84%
So it's not like gold
that closes on Friday

00:50:22.760 --> 00:50:25.010 align:middle line:84%
and doesn't open, gap up
or gap down, on Monday.

00:50:25.010 --> 00:50:25.810 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:50:25.810 --> 00:50:28.410 align:middle line:90%
It's open 24/7.

00:50:28.410 --> 00:50:29.729 align:middle line:90%
A unit of accounting.

00:50:29.729 --> 00:50:31.270 align:middle line:84%
Some of these coins
you're getting so

00:50:31.270 --> 00:50:33.790 align:middle line:84%
developed that we can have
smart contracts on them.

00:50:33.790 --> 00:50:38.650 align:middle line:84%
So let's say that Target has
a coin, an Ethereum coin.

00:50:38.650 --> 00:50:41.680 align:middle line:84%
And they have an agreement
with a supplier in China,

00:50:41.680 --> 00:50:44.420 align:middle line:84%
that when a certain
condition is met,

00:50:44.420 --> 00:50:48.070 align:middle line:84%
the supplier scans the code, it
triggers the payment to Target.

00:50:48.070 --> 00:50:51.080 align:middle line:84%
Or Target triggers the
payment to the supplier.

00:50:51.080 --> 00:50:53.500 align:middle line:84%
And so these things
take-- literally the banks

00:50:53.500 --> 00:50:55.540 align:middle line:90%
become dumb pipelines.

00:50:55.540 --> 00:50:57.760 align:middle line:84%
One of the big issues with
the last financial crisis

00:50:57.760 --> 00:50:59.430 align:middle line:90%
was letters of credit.

00:50:59.430 --> 00:51:01.630 align:middle line:84%
That if the banks
are not solvent,

00:51:01.630 --> 00:51:05.140 align:middle line:84%
then how is the manufacturer,
distributor, warehouse dude

00:51:05.140 --> 00:51:07.030 align:middle line:90%
going to get paid for his work?

00:51:07.030 --> 00:51:09.280 align:middle line:84%
If all of a sudden that
big bank letter of credit

00:51:09.280 --> 00:51:10.624 align:middle line:90%
it isn't any good.

00:51:10.624 --> 00:51:12.790 align:middle line:84%
And this is where the
blockchain and these cryptos--

00:51:12.790 --> 00:51:14.581 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Because it
circumvents the banks.

00:51:14.581 --> 00:51:16.420 align:middle line:84%
But doesn't this
necessarily mean a bank,

00:51:16.420 --> 00:51:18.460 align:middle line:84%
if enough people
bought into it, this

00:51:18.460 --> 00:51:21.250 align:middle line:84%
means the banks would
essentially become--

00:51:21.250 --> 00:51:22.270 align:middle line:90%
>>STEVENS: Dumb.

00:51:22.270 --> 00:51:23.560 align:middle line:90%
Dumb and useless.

00:51:23.560 --> 00:51:27.407 align:middle line:84%
And so 90%-plus of their
workforce will be let go.

00:51:27.407 --> 00:51:28.990 align:middle line:84%
And so how are they
going to get paid?

00:51:28.990 --> 00:51:30.406 align:middle line:84%
Well, I've got a
computer at home.

00:51:30.406 --> 00:51:32.140 align:middle line:90%
I've got to join the revolution.

00:51:32.140 --> 00:51:34.540 align:middle line:84%
And then they have
to start working.

00:51:34.540 --> 00:51:37.570 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So how much of this
requires-- in your opinion,

00:51:37.570 --> 00:51:40.000 align:middle line:90%
you've dealt with it-- faith?

00:51:40.000 --> 00:51:41.140 align:middle line:90%
Faith in the system?

00:51:41.140 --> 00:51:42.490 align:middle line:90%
Faith in the coins?

00:51:42.490 --> 00:51:45.380 align:middle line:84%
>>STEVENS: What base-- what
is the basis of our dollar?

00:51:45.380 --> 00:51:48.156 align:middle line:84%
Full failing credit of the
United States government.

00:51:48.156 --> 00:51:49.030 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: It is true.

00:51:49.030 --> 00:51:50.613 align:middle line:84%
But it's just been
a perpetual pattern

00:51:50.613 --> 00:51:52.489 align:middle line:84%
for so long, that people,
kind of by default,

00:51:52.489 --> 00:51:54.113 align:middle line:84%
have faith that you
can go to the store

00:51:54.113 --> 00:51:55.420 align:middle line:90%
and get something with it.

00:51:55.420 --> 00:51:58.540 align:middle line:84%
But in this, where they can't
see it, touch it or understand

00:51:58.540 --> 00:51:59.340 align:middle line:90%
it, exactly--

00:51:59.340 --> 00:52:01.480 align:middle line:84%
>>STEVENS: And yet my
debit card, I can't see,

00:52:01.480 --> 00:52:02.710 align:middle line:90%
touch any of that.

00:52:02.710 --> 00:52:04.360 align:middle line:90%
It's the same thing.

00:52:04.360 --> 00:52:07.810 align:middle line:84%
Except-- how do I
want to say this?--

00:52:07.810 --> 00:52:11.950 align:middle line:84%
when you go to a consumer or a
vendor or a merchant that takes

00:52:11.950 --> 00:52:15.520 align:middle line:84%
Bitcoin, more likely than not,
they will give you a discount

00:52:15.520 --> 00:52:17.260 align:middle line:90%
for using Bitcoin.

00:52:17.260 --> 00:52:20.650 align:middle line:84%
Simply because the
value of the Bitcoin

00:52:20.650 --> 00:52:24.790 align:middle line:90%
will go up while they hold it.

00:52:24.790 --> 00:52:26.500 align:middle line:84%
Because they have
that much faith in it.

00:52:26.500 --> 00:52:27.760 align:middle line:90%
Overstock.com one of them.

00:52:27.760 --> 00:52:28.561 align:middle line:90%
Not to drop names.

00:52:28.561 --> 00:52:30.518 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: No, I was going
to ask you to give us

00:52:30.518 --> 00:52:32.500 align:middle line:84%
the name of several
companies that are actually

00:52:32.500 --> 00:52:33.200 align:middle line:90%
accepting Bitcoin.

00:52:33.200 --> 00:52:34.000 align:middle line:90%
>>STEVENS: Amazon.

00:52:34.000 --> 00:52:34.870 align:middle line:90%
Newegg.

00:52:34.870 --> 00:52:35.830 align:middle line:90%
Microsoft.

00:52:35.830 --> 00:52:39.010 align:middle line:84%
Microsoft, their whole
cloud-based platform, Azure,

00:52:39.010 --> 00:52:41.200 align:middle line:90%
is going to be Ethereum-based.

00:52:41.200 --> 00:52:42.940 align:middle line:84%
So that they don't
have to have people

00:52:42.940 --> 00:52:45.040 align:middle line:84%
in there dealing with
contracts and managing this.

00:52:45.040 --> 00:52:47.690 align:middle line:84%
This is all going to
be done by-- honestly,

00:52:47.690 --> 00:52:51.370 align:middle line:84%
it will be all our computers
running the Ethereum network.

00:52:51.370 --> 00:52:55.510 align:middle line:84%
And so, for us devoting our
computer-- 90% of our computing

00:52:55.510 --> 00:52:57.910 align:middle line:84%
processor-- to these
coins, mining these coins,

00:52:57.910 --> 00:53:00.640 align:middle line:84%
securing these networks,
dealing with the transactions,

00:53:00.640 --> 00:53:04.280 align:middle line:84%
we get rewarded by an
aspect of that currency.

00:53:04.280 --> 00:53:06.730 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So it's a true
democratization of money.

00:53:06.730 --> 00:53:09.280 align:middle line:84%
>>STEVENS: It's
decentralized money.

00:53:09.280 --> 00:53:11.410 align:middle line:90%
And that will set us free.

00:53:11.410 --> 00:53:14.820 align:middle line:84%
Free from the tyranny
of these banks.

00:53:14.820 --> 00:53:17.410 align:middle line:84%
And I hope it doesn't
take a crisis,

00:53:17.410 --> 00:53:18.620 align:middle line:90%
but more than likely it does.

00:53:18.620 --> 00:53:19.420 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Probably.

00:53:19.420 --> 00:53:21.370 align:middle line:84%
>>STEVENS: It is that
which moves us out

00:53:21.370 --> 00:53:23.550 align:middle line:90%
of our comfort zone.

00:53:23.550 --> 00:53:25.925 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And tying
this all back together,

00:53:25.925 --> 00:53:28.510 align:middle line:84%
you originally said
that the chemtrails

00:53:28.510 --> 00:53:31.600 align:middle line:84%
will stop when the
monetary benefit to them

00:53:31.600 --> 00:53:32.800 align:middle line:90%
is no longer there.

00:53:32.800 --> 00:53:35.570 align:middle line:84%
Meaning when you can't control
large sums of money in the way

00:53:35.570 --> 00:53:36.370 align:middle line:90%
they have been.

00:53:36.370 --> 00:53:37.330 align:middle line:90%
The movement of money.

00:53:37.330 --> 00:53:38.829 align:middle line:84%
>>STEVENS: Meaning
when those planes

00:53:38.829 --> 00:53:42.400 align:middle line:84%
can't get the fuel because
the money system isn't there.

00:53:42.400 --> 00:53:46.030 align:middle line:84%
When Boeing and Lockheed
and Lear and Gulfstream

00:53:46.030 --> 00:53:49.390 align:middle line:84%
and Bombardier, and all these
aircraft companies can't get

00:53:49.390 --> 00:53:51.944 align:middle line:84%
paid via the dollar
to build the aircraft.

00:53:51.944 --> 00:53:53.860 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Meaning if
they were-- they probably

00:53:53.860 --> 00:53:55.651 align:middle line:84%
wouldn't be paid if
their transactions were

00:53:55.651 --> 00:53:56.680 align:middle line:90%
made transparent, right?

00:53:56.680 --> 00:53:57.400 align:middle line:90%
>>STEVENS: Thank you.

00:53:57.400 --> 00:53:57.730 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:53:57.730 --> 00:53:59.646 align:middle line:84%
When they had to do a
full accounting, because

00:53:59.646 --> 00:54:02.160 align:middle line:84%
of the blockchain, of where
their resources, their moneys

00:54:02.160 --> 00:54:02.960 align:middle line:90%
are coming from.

00:54:02.960 --> 00:54:06.070 align:middle line:84%
Because the dark
pool then disappears.

00:54:06.070 --> 00:54:07.240 align:middle line:90%
I mean, yes and no.

00:54:07.240 --> 00:54:09.850 align:middle line:84%
I mean, you can
have other layers,

00:54:09.850 --> 00:54:11.560 align:middle line:84%
but that value in
this dark layer

00:54:11.560 --> 00:54:15.790 align:middle line:84%
has got to come into this
transparent system eventually.

00:54:15.790 --> 00:54:17.532 align:middle line:90%
Eventually.

00:54:17.532 --> 00:54:19.990 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: It's the first time
I've heard someone explain it

00:54:19.990 --> 00:54:22.000 align:middle line:84%
in this particular
way, you know,

00:54:22.000 --> 00:54:23.860 align:middle line:84%
rather than just
trying to explain

00:54:23.860 --> 00:54:26.390 align:middle line:90%
how this thing exists at all.

00:54:26.390 --> 00:54:29.799 align:middle line:84%
>>STEVENS: And that's still kind
of mysteriously cool, in a way.

00:54:29.799 --> 00:54:31.840 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, yeah, I
mean, I still can't quite

00:54:31.840 --> 00:54:34.390 align:middle line:84%
get my mind around it,
looking in a digital way

00:54:34.390 --> 00:54:35.590 align:middle line:90%
through the maze.

00:54:35.590 --> 00:54:39.100 align:middle line:84%
What happens, though,
in terms of fears

00:54:39.100 --> 00:54:43.430 align:middle line:84%
of if the poo really hits the
fan and the grid goes down?

00:54:43.430 --> 00:54:44.230 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:54:44.230 --> 00:54:46.563 align:middle line:84%
>>STEVENS: I don't think the
grid will go down entirely.

00:54:46.563 --> 00:54:49.669 align:middle line:84%
I think there will be periods of
time where it comes in and out.

00:54:49.669 --> 00:54:51.460 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: How do you
do transactions when--

00:54:51.460 --> 00:54:54.430 align:middle line:84%
>>STEVENS: They need it
more than that we need it.

00:54:54.430 --> 00:54:55.960 align:middle line:84%
I mean, they need
it to watch us.

00:54:55.960 --> 00:54:57.810 align:middle line:84%
They need it to
keep their sniffers

00:54:57.810 --> 00:54:59.860 align:middle line:90%
and their awareness-- the NSA.

00:54:59.860 --> 00:55:02.860 align:middle line:84%
The system needs it up and
operating, otherwise they

00:55:02.860 --> 00:55:04.464 align:middle line:90%
lose control of us.

00:55:04.464 --> 00:55:06.130 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: What happens
if it's something

00:55:06.130 --> 00:55:07.300 align:middle line:90%
even beyond their control?

00:55:07.300 --> 00:55:08.425 align:middle line:90%
Beyond anyone's control?

00:55:08.425 --> 00:55:08.930 align:middle line:90%
Natural forces.

00:55:08.930 --> 00:55:11.305 align:middle line:84%
>>STEVENS: And I anticipate
that that's what will happen.

00:55:11.305 --> 00:55:13.315 align:middle line:90%
The ATMs will be dark, too.

00:55:13.315 --> 00:55:14.190 align:middle line:90%
They'll be dark, too.

00:55:14.190 --> 00:55:17.500 align:middle line:84%
But, because this is a
decentralized system,

00:55:17.500 --> 00:55:20.950 align:middle line:84%
there'll still be a server
running in South Africa.

00:55:20.950 --> 00:55:23.920 align:middle line:90%
Still managing the blockchain.

00:55:23.920 --> 00:55:26.890 align:middle line:84%
And one in India,
maybe one in Sri Lanka.

00:55:26.890 --> 00:55:29.290 align:middle line:84%
And then when the system
reboots, comes back on,

00:55:29.290 --> 00:55:30.880 align:middle line:84%
other people connect,
infrastructure

00:55:30.880 --> 00:55:32.872 align:middle line:90%
gets rebuilt-- there it is.

00:55:32.872 --> 00:55:34.330 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But in
the interim, you'd

00:55:34.330 --> 00:55:35.535 align:middle line:84%
better have your
own heirloom seeds

00:55:35.535 --> 00:55:36.590 align:middle line:90%
and have your own chickens.

00:55:36.590 --> 00:55:38.140 align:middle line:84%
>>STEVENS: Yeah, that's why
we have our food closet.

00:55:38.140 --> 00:55:39.376 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:55:39.376 --> 00:55:40.200 align:middle line:90%
Absolutely.

00:55:40.200 --> 00:55:42.408 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: When we were
talking off-camera about this,

00:55:42.408 --> 00:55:45.790 align:middle line:84%
